title: Phillipsburg girls soccer team shuts out rival Easton
text:
A first-half penalty kick from Phillipsburg ’s Sydney Solimani was everything the Stateliners girls soccer team needed to knock off rival Easton 1-0 on Saturday at the Phillipsburg Athletic Complex. 
Antonia Russo made 12 saves for Phillipsburg in the shutout. 
The victory is the Stateliners’ fourth of the season. Easton (13-5-1) finished atop the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference Steel Division. Back to back! The girls soccer team beats Easton by a score of 1-0. #beateaston pic.twitter.com/716tm0GqTE — Phillipsburg Soccer (@SoccerPHSGirls) October 24, 2015 Toni Russo is named the MVP for her shut out. Sydney Solimani had the lone goal of the match! pic.twitter.com/4OrhBHgeIc
